[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
“...Yes, Chito will join me shortly. Ishii-san, please reunite with your parents first... alright, thank you.”[l][r]

[_tb_end_text]

[playse  volume="100"  time="1000"  buf="0"  storage="mobile-phone-pickup1.ogg"  ]
[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
[r]I finished the call and checked the time. It felt long, but not really.[r]
I shoved the phone into my pocket and searched for my pack of cigarettes... Oh, right, I quit smoking.[l][r]
The convenience store wasn’t far if I drove, but I decided against it. I placed my hand on the steering wheel and tapped a random rhythm.[l][r]
Anything, I needed something to distract myself.[l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[cm  ]
[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
Rain pelted the windshield. The wiper's sound filled the car, and I just waited, spacey.[l][r]
I checked the clock again. It had been about five minutes since my wife went to fetch Chito. They should be back soon.[l][r]
I looked at the rearview mirror and saw two figures. After a short while, my wife and Chito got in the car.[l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[playse  volume="100"  time="1000"  buf="0"  storage="car-door-open1.ogg"  ]
[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
[r]“Sorry for the wait, Kanazawa.”[l][r]
“It's fine, I didn’t wait long. Plus, the rain must have been tough.”[l][r]
“No, it’s okay. More importantly... where is Yuu?”[l][r]
[r]Chito looked at me through the mirror. I took a deep breath. It felt like holding the switch to a bomb.[l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[cm  ]
[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
“...Please stay calm and listen.” I said.[l][r]
“...Alright.”[r]
Chito replied without much hesitation. Did she sense what she was about to hear? Poor thing.[l][r]
I wondered why such a young girl had to become so wise.[l][r]
Just a normal girl who should be laughing with friends, playing, worrying about grades and love, nothing special.[l][r]
[r]I closed my eyes once, bracing myself. Like flipping a switch, I began,[l]
[r]“Yuri is... in the hospital.”[l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

